# Security & Secrets

- Never commit `.env`, API keys, tokens, or passwords. Use `.env.example` with placeholders.
- Hash passwords with bcrypt; store refresh token hashes only, never plaintext tokens.
- Validate and sanitize all user input via Pydantic (backend) and form validation (frontend).
- Enforce authorization in the service layer; return 404 (not 403) when hiding resource existence.
- No `eval`, unsafe deserialization, permissive CORS, or auth bypasses.
- CSV export scoped to current user's own created tickets only.
